In case you missed them, here are the other trailers we covered at         /Film this week:


 
	The Deep Blue Sea Trailer [1] - A sad, broken love story that you just know won't end well? I'll be right there.
	Being Elmo: A Puppeteer's Journey Trailer  [2]- Looks like one of the true feel-good movies of the year and there's nothing wrong with that.
	John Dies At The End Trailer [3] -I would actually like to see this. Seems to have a certain style and zip all its own.
	One For The Money Trailer [4] - I can't believe someone wrote a check with a whole lot of zeroes at the end of it to make this pile.
	Sleepless Night Trailer [5] - Looks absolutely nuts and I'm looking forward to it.
	New Year's Eve Trailer #2 [6] - I'd rather have a ramrod plunged into the small of my back than to see one frame of this film.
	Paranormal Activity 3 Trailer #2 [7] - I'm not sure about the movie but this trailer manages to be interesting and exciting. Color me impressed.
	6 Days To Air Trailer [8] - To watch this beehive move at the clip that it does is to witness true creative energy at work.
	Extremely Loud and Incredibly Close Trailer [9] - I see nothing but emotional manipulation if I were to enter a pact to see this film. Not interested.
	The Thing International Trailer [10] - I know this film is completely unnecessary but I like this version of the trailer simply for how in-depth it gets with the actual gore. 2 points Russia.
	I Melt With You Trailer [11] - This is a great trailer, flat out. If it's hiding a truly horrible film, one of the worst of the year, then whoever made this needs an extra pack of Skittles in his paycheck.



 






